# Todo List

## Starting the server

In a command line, navigate to the `todo-app/server` directory and run the following commands:
```
$ npm i
$ npm start
```

By default, this will start the todo-app server listening on port 3001

## Starting the app

### Building for production

In a command line, navigate to the `todo-app/client` directory and run the following commands:
```
$ npm i
$ npm run build
```

This will compile the app into the `todo-app/client/dist` directory

### Building for development

In a command line, navigate to the `todo-app/client` directory and run the following commands:
```
$ npm i
$ npm start
```

This will start the todo-app in development mode and will be available at http://localhost:3000
